		Building Opentracker

Opentracker builds with CMake, which you must have installed. Additionally, you
will need a suitable installation of libowfat (http://www.fefe.de/libowfat/)
and depending on the build configuration, zlib, zstd, and libbsd (on Linux).

	apt install build-essential git cmake libowfat-dev zlib1g-dev libzstd-dev libbsd-dev
	dnf install cmake gcc git libowfat-devel zlib-devel libzstd-devel libbsd-devel

Building opentracker in the default configuration is usually just a matter of
running

	cmake -S . -B build
	make -C build
	./build/opentracker

or if you plan to install globally, you can do

	cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -S . -B build
	make -C build install
	opentracker

You can also build in debug mode, which will compile in some additional debug
facilities

	cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -S . -B build
	make -C build


		Customizing Opentracker

The default build configuration should be suitable for most people. If you want
additional features, like accesslists or clustering support, you can build
opentracker with the appropriate build options enabled.

	cmake -DWANT_ACCESSLIST_BLACK=Y -S . -B build

You can also disable build options.

	cmake -DWANT_COMPRESSION_GZIP=N -S . -B build

Here's a summary of all of the build options currently supported.

	WANT_V4_ONLY
		Compile opentracker with IPv4 only (without IPv6).

	WANT_ACCESSLIST_BLACK
		Enable support for configuring a torrent blacklist file.

	WANT_ACCESSLIST_WHITE
		Enable support for configuring a torrent whitelist file.

	WANT_DYNAMIC_ACCESSLIST
		Enable support for dynamic access lists, with fifo allowing to add or
		delete torrents.

	WANT_COMPRESSION_ZSTD
		Compile opentracker with support for zstd compression. Requires libzstd.

	WANT_COMPRESSION_ZSTD_ALWAYS
		Configure opentracker to always offer zstd compression when serving
		requests. Requires WANT_COMPRESSION_ZSTD.

	WANT_COMPRESSION_GZIP
		Compile opentracker with support for gzip compression. Requires zlib.
		Enabled by default.

	WANT_COMPRESSION_GZIP_ALWAYS
		Configure opentracker to always offer gzip compression when serving
		requests. Requires WANT_COMPRESSION_GZIP.

	WANT_SYNC_LIVE
		Build opentracker to run in a cluster.

	WANT_IP_FROM_QUERY_STRING
		Configure opentracker to use peer addresses from the appropriate query
		string in announce requests. Recommended only for debugging purposes.

	WANT_IP_FROM_PROXY (Experimental)
		Use peer address from proxy variables.

	WANT_LOG_NETWORKS (Experimental)
		Log networks.

	WANT_RESTRICT_STATS
		Restrict access to sensitive stats endpoint, blessing source addresses
		through configuration.

	WANT_FULLLOG_NETWORKS
		Undocumented.

	WANT_LOG_NUMWANT
		Undocumented.

	WANT_MODEST_FULLSCRAPES
		Undocumented.

	WANT_SPOT_WOODPECKER
		Undocumented.

	WANT_SYSLOGS
		Enable logging to syslog.

	WANT_DEV_RANDOM
		Use srandomdev (BSD). On Linux, requires libbsd.

	WANT_ARC4RANDOM
		Use arc4random (BSD). On Linux, requires libbsd.

	WANT_FULLSCRAPE
		Enable fullscrapes to allow clients to query for all tracked torrents.
		Enabled by default.

	WANT_NO_AUTO_FREE
		Configure opentracker to disable automatic release of chunks during full
		scrape transfer. Enabled by default for libowfat <0.34.

	WANT_STATIC_LIBOWFAT
		Link against static libowfat library. Enabled by default.

	_DEBUG_HTTPERROR (Debug)
		Log HTTP errors.

	_DEBUG_RANDOMTORRENTS (Debug)
		Generate random peers and torrents at startup for testing.


		Building with libowfat Source Builds

If libowfat isn't available in your environment and you're building it from
source, you can help CMake find it with CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH:

	cvs -d :pserver:cvs@cvs.fefe.de:/cvs -z9 co libowfat
	cd libowfat
	make

	cd ../opentracker
	CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=../libowfat cmake -S . -B build
	make -C build
